Reposting these powerful words about mothers from @yvettenicolebrown, who appeared on @jhillunbothered last October. YNB had recently lost her mother so I appreciated her candor and vulnerability. 

Obviously on Mother’s Day, it’s important to celebrate our mothers, grandmothers, aunts, bonus Moms and mother figures. But it’s equally important to support friends and loved ones who have lost their mothers, or have difficult relationships with their mother. We also need to check in on mothers who have lost their children. 

Happy Mother’s Day ❤️

(*If you want to listen to the full pod, LINK IS IN MY BIO)

My guest this week on @jhillunbothered is @abbydphillip, host of CNN’s Inside Politics and senior political correspondent. Abby shares how outrage is destroying the political system, what it was like co-moderating the presidential debate, the ins and outs of covering the White House, how she went from studying pre-med at Harvard to political journalism, and how Donald Trump made political journalists better. Plus, I share my thoughts on the people cheering the demise of CNN+.

To listen, CLICK THE LINK IN MY BIO.

Reposting these powerful words about mothers from @yvettenicolebrown, who appeared on @jhillunbothered last October. YNB had recently lost her mother so I appreciated her candor and vulnerability. 

Obviously on Mother’s Day, it’s important to celebrate our mothers, grandmothers, aunts, bonus Moms and mother figures. But it’s equally important to support friends and loved ones who have lost their mothers, or have difficult relationships with their mother. We also need to check in on mothers who have lost their children. 

Happy Mother’s Day ❤️

(*If you want to listen to the full pod, LINK IS IN MY BIO)

My guest this week on @jhillunbothered is @abbydphillip, host of CNN’s Inside Politics and senior political correspondent. Plus, I share my thoughts on the people cheering the demise of CNN+.

node.text: This is one of my favorite conversations that I’ve ever had on @jhillunbothered. My homie @danamo joins me to discuss her new book, Shine Bright: A Very Personal History of Black Women In Pop (which is SENSATIONAL). We discuss her incredible origin story, best concerts she’s ever attended, and being the first black editor in chief at Vibe magazine. To listen, CLICK THE LINK IN MY BIO.

node.text:
I’ve never had a slurpee or Frozen Coke from 7-Eleven or anywhere else.

I’ve never had iced coffee because the idea of cold coffee seems so trash.

Give me your answer in the comments.

Last night @bebewinans @cecewinans @imericacampbell @therealmarymary took us to church and then some during their @verzuztv performance. Can’t thank our friends @deborahjoywinans @tjwill33 for the invite and for introducing me to fellow Mumford alum @cecewinans for the first time (FYI … both BeBe and CeCe are mighty Mustangs). What a show! What a time!

node.text: My guest on this week’s episode of @jhillunbothered is the fabulous @cocojones. To listen, LINK IA IN MY BIO.

It was such a blast attending the @appletvplus premiere of @magicjohnson’s upcoming docuseries “They Call Me Magic.” It really is incredible. But that after-party … Magic took us back to a good, old-fashioned house parties. I’m going to need to soak my feet today because they’re so sore from dancing!
